{
  "stem": "21626.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 77.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "In fact, Joe Placek, who then took on the name Joe Alon-- he was the Air Attache for Israel in Washington and was assassinated some years back.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And there's a museum dedicated to him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you know-- and only about a year ago, I was in a restaurant in England.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And next to me there were a couple of guys who were obvious Israeli pilots, flying from Israel here.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so I started talking to them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I said-- I asked them if they, by any chance, knew Joe.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They said, know him?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He's a legend.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he taught us all we know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I felt very proud.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I've digressed a bit, but I thought it was important little story.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when the communists took over-- or rather, before they took over-- I was offered a job of being trained to be a secretary to the military attache in Washington an-- or in London.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I jumped at it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was, by then, studying at [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Brock ?] University, at Charles University.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was 1948-- 1947. 1947, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I took on this job only a month before the coup d'etat, before the communist takeover.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "During that month, I was in charge of confidential information, which came to the Ministry of Defense-- I was working in the Ministry of Defense-- from France and from England.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was a translation pool.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I marked the articles and that which were to be translated, you know, and handed them out.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well of course, after the coup d'etat, you can imagine, I was an anti-communist, pro-British, of bourgeois origin, and commun-- and Jewish, to boot.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was very much a persona non grata.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Moreover, I never learned to keep my mouth shut, because I grew up in free England.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
